author: Tara Bellucci
title: Before & After: IKEA Cabinet Turned West Elm-Inspired Buffet
text:
(Image credit: Aniko Levai ) 
Aniko's white IKEA wall unit worked fine in the dining room. But the second she saw West Elm's reclaimed wood buffet , she knew she could refresh this basic piece into a showstopperâ€”and save over $1,100 in the process. (Image credit: Aniko Levai ) 
Aniko got the wood for free from a local business, and spent $17 on stain and lacquer. That's a pretty hefty savings! 
Check out her blog, A Place of My Taste , for more photos and a tutorial on how she made the oversized art that hangs above her new buffet. 
Thank you, Aniko!
